

VtSet(1vtcl)                                         VtSet(1vtcl)

SSyynnooppssiiss
       VtSet widgetName [options]
       VtSetValues widgetName [options]

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       Used to set the value of a widget option.  The option name
       used is the same option used  in  widget  creation.   Only
       options  which  have  an  S next to the option name in the
       command reference can be set with VtSet.

   OOppttiioonnss
       Use any valid options for the particular widget. xmArgs to
       pass  X resources to the server.  For example: VtSetValues
       $myLabel -label foo Sets the label string of  $myLabel  to
       ``foo''.

RReettuurrnn vvaalluueess
       If VtSet fails, it returns one of the following error mes-
       sages: the option is not settable

NNoottiicceess
       VtSetFocus and VtSetSensitive  remain  available  in  this
       release for backward compatibility.

       Please  use VtSet with the appropriate options rather than
       VtSetFocus or VtSetSensitive to ensure forward compatibil-
       ity.

       For  VtSetFocus,  use: VtSet -takeFocus VtSet -focusDirec-
       tion

       For VtSetSensitive, use: VtSet -sensitive

